version_description: The correct chords for the acoustic version.
Full Chord Tab of song. Please rate or comment.

Difference from other tabs - (in 4 words: much easier to read)  Full, lyrics and instrumental chords. Maintained the integrity and structure of the lyrics - much easier to read. Correct rubric - the song is difficult to read in previous forms. Riffs and matching chords.
Added chords to final chorus. Added tuning.
Good acoustic version that I use to play out with all the time. I have not seen any other version with the Edim7 chord, which I believe is correct to my ear.

Great song, great band, great era. So here's my way of one-man-banding Sex Type Thing, the intro and interlude are actually played together in the original so if you have friends you can do that. The F#m/E throughout the verse is basically just the F#m barre chord hammering on and off with the index finger and throwing some muted strums in there for flavour.
This is a very simple version of the song which is ideal for singing over whilst playing on an acoustic.

song_name: Trippin On A Hole In A Paper Heart
